1. Objective¶

This analysis intends to provide recommendations to a prospective tenant who wishes to decide upon an appropriate property to rent given a set of preferences like location, capacity of occupancy, number of days to rent etc.

Alternately , this analysis also helps in understanding the pricing trend of properties on Airbnb which provides information to rental property owners who would potentially wish to sublet on Airbnb in New York City.

3.1.2 Treating null values & Converting Response Time in hours:¶

Since the number of Hosts which no response time recorded (null values = 6392) is more than the majority ) response time which is "within an hour". We assume the response time for null values also to be within an hour.

In [351]:
#replace nan in Host Response Time = majority 
Response_time = df_host['Host Response Time'].unique()
Response_time

# 'within an hour' = 1
# 'within a day' = 24
# 'within a few hours'=12
# 'a few days or more' = 72
Out[351]:
array(['within an hour', nan, 'within a day', 'within a few hours',
       'a few days or more'], dtype=object)
In [352]:
# create new column with response in hours

def resp (row):
#    if(row == 'within an hour'):
#        return 1
    if(row == 'within a day'):
        return 24
    if(row == 'within a few hours'):
        return 12
    if(row == 'a few days or more'):
        return 72
    return 1

df_host['Host Response Hours'] = df_host['Host Response Time'].apply(lambda row: resp(row))

3.1.3 Summary of Host Information :¶

  1. There were 6392 blank records in the Host Response Time.
  2. Host Response Time in raw data is recorded in hours and days.
  3. For those with recorded response time, majority response is within an hour.
  4. Treating outliers : Missing values could be because they were never reported. So we are in this case treating outliers with average response value to maintain neutrality

6. Conclusion of Exploratory Data Analysis¶

Summary¶

  1. This most noticable variations in price is due to Neighbourhood location and Room Type.

  2. Manhattan is the most expensive for all types of properties. The main influence here is it being a prime location for Business as well as Entertainment. This overpowers the nature of the appartment like bed and baths.

  3. Additionally, price property spaces vary with neighbourhood location. For instance, Apartments in Bronx and Staten Island are priced lower compared to apartments in Manhattan and Brooklyn.

  4. Another great influencer is Room Type. Shared and Private rooms are inexpensive compared to Entire property space.

Challenges :¶

  • The greatest influence of Price of a property is the season and location.
  • Holiday seasons, always see a high rise in prices
  • Location plays a major role as well in terms to determine the price. For instance, a riverside property will be more expensive than an inland property.
  • The relationship of price with most of the features is non-linear.

Therefore the greatest challenge of the analysis is lack of seasonal data. However, in this analysi we attempt to estimate the price of a property based on its features and ratings.
